original: Lindqvist, Knut Inge Håkan, "^yi’-koherde, Anten, f. 2/12/14 i Borås av landskont. Albert L. o. Lydia Relan-der. G. 41 m. Brit, f. Lindqvist. Barn : Eva f. 44, Thomas 47. Stud:ex. i Vä-nersb. 35, teol. fil. ex. 36, teol. kand. 39 prakt. teol. prov o. prästv. f. Skara stift 40. Past:adj. i Trollhättan 40, sv. sjömanspastor i Stettin o. Kiel, Tyskl., 41, pas’t :adj. i Skara 44, kyrkoh. i Långared, Älvsb. h, sed. 45. Ordf. i Långareds RK-krets sed. 45, i kyrkostämman ’sed. 46.
translated: Lindqvist, Knut Inge Håkan, "^yi’-koherde, Anten, b. 2/12/14 in Borås to Albert L. and Lydia Relander. Married in 1941 to Brit Lindqvist. Children: Eva b. 1944, Thomas b. 1947. Graduated from Vänersborgs gymnasium in 1935, received a degree in theology in 1936, completed practical theology examinations and was ordained as a priest in the Skara Diocese in 1940. Served as assistant pastor in Trollhättan in 1940, Swedish seafarer's pastor in Stettin and Kiel, Germany, in 1941, and as assistant pastor in Skara in 1944. Became the church pastor in Långared, Älvsborg County in 1945. Chairman of the Långared RK District since 1945, and in the church assembly since 1946.
